    "text": "A challenge qualifies as fundamental only if it is unavoidable for general embodied agents, not when it arises as a design choice for a particular solution.",
    "topic": "Fundamental challenge criterion"
  },
  {
    "text": "Partial observability and overwritten world states are the foundational problems; memory-to-plan translation is a downstream implementation tactic.",
